 I know, old topic, but I just had a perfect example yesterday when I was asked to join a Guardian group in PoN.<br>
<br>
I was discussing with the SK if he wanted me to snare the mob or if he was going to take care of it.  He asked me to take care of it because for some reason it liked resisting his &quot;snare&quot; (He was also 3 levels below me.. I'm 61 he was 5<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . <br>
<br>
That's all fine, cept then the cleric comes in (The group leader) instructing me when to snare, not to snare to early cause I'd agro the mob.. not to nuke to hard cause I'd agro the mob and die. (This isn't the first time I've heard this type of thing).<br>
<br>
What the?? Why does a cleric need to tell me how to do my job?  Last time I checked I was the wizard.. thing is, this isn't uncommon.  To many Wizards over nuke, don't know how to use a simple spell like Concussion (And any wizard who's above 51 that doesn't have it is crazy) and just don't know ANYthing about agro/crowd control.<br>
<br>
After that discussion, the SK pulled (good pull) but for some reason the second Guardian agro'd on us.  The second wizard in the group (He was 53) ran from the group.. I cast evac and boom we were at the zone in , and everyone cept for the other wizzy (Who decided to run as I said before) was alive and kicking.  I was getting tells from the whole group sayin &quot;Wow, what a wizard&quot; and stuff like that.  Again WTH?  Isn't that our job, shouldn't EVERYONE be doing that type of thing??<br>
<br>
On another note, I haven't played in over a year, and a lot of things are new to me, but still, our job hasn't changed at all in the 4 years that my characters have been around!! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=izlaaru>Izlaaru</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 182<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/9/03 11:39 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why wizards can't get groups...</span><hr size=1> Hrm, can't seem to find an Edit command, so here's my Edit:<br>
<br>
This is why (I believe) that I sit in PoD LFG for 2 hours while I quad junk!!! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  (Quading can get really boring after a while) <p>&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13354&quot; target =&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;img border=&quot;0&quot; src=&quot;http://members.home.com/candon/Signature.jpg&quot; width=&quot;339&quot; height=&quot;67&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=isammumiau>Isammu Miau</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/9/03 2:28 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why wizards can't get groups...</span><hr size=1> I think it’s all about people thinking they know a lot but they really don’t.<br>
I have played for a long time and have seen it all. If someone posted on a major board that bards sucked then it was law. Within a few days bards everywhere were being kicked out of groups and made fun off.<br>
<br>
I play on stromm now and even there you have people at level7 FFS saying they won’t group rangers or wizards for X amount of reasons. I mean damn at level 7?!!!<br>
<br>
I can understand if the group needs to fill key spots first like tank, healer, crowd control,<br>
But after that really in 90% of EQ zones it doesn’t matter who your 5th and 6th man are.<br>
<br>
Some people just like to pick a class and bash it for not reason kind of like people who have ford cars hate chevy or Nissan vs Toyota stupid crap like that.<br>
<br>
As for people telling you how to play well everyone thinks they are good at what they do and if they have even seen a good player play they will compare you to him or her. I just stay quiet when this happens and let them chat away, unless it is imported info like zone info or traps or stuff.<br>
<br>
But people telling me what to nuke and when and how much they can kiss off I will do the best I can and not get myself or my group killed but besides that I do as I want within reason.<br>
<br>
There are exceptions to every rule but I don’t mind a leader running down what peoples rolls are but some gimp on a pick-up group telling you how to play is stupid.<br>
 <p>Nerezza Cadute <br>
Level 4<br>
Dark Elf Wizard<br>
