Not grouping with X class at level 7 because X class can't do whatever, is pretty funny, because basically everyone is a warrior at that level. Heck, priests don't even get med until 8. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=euphrates>Euphrates</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/10/03 3:05 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why wizards can't get groups...</span><hr size=1> I am a cleric and if I am leading a group and a wizard in it snares on inc, possibly getting aggro and making me waste mana on them, I will say something.  If the snare breaks just before the mob reaches run life because you cast it too soon, I am going to say something unpleasant.  If the wizard is using strike of solusek (or any eye candy nuke) instead of draughts/rains/other more efficient nukes because they like big crits, then I will say something.  If the wizard isn't using concussion ENOUGH, I will say something.  If the wizard takes offense to me saying something, they can find themself another group.  I don't just rip into people before they fuck up though.  Pretty much if you are a wizard and you get enough aggro to take damage beyond your epic rune, you suck.  Exceptions being adds and other extenuating circumstances. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thalaan>Thalaan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 121<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/10/03 3:24 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why wizards can't get groups...</span><hr size=1> Euphrates, retard clerics like you are why we are constantly LFG. People with set ideas, never open to change.  I hope the wizards grouping with you are telling you what spells to memorise too.<br>
<br>
Not all wizards have concussion, are you going to discriminate against them because of it? (I lost my VS faction before i was able to quest it)<br>
<br>
I know my job. you do yours, and heal.  Occasionally rezz yourself what YOU fuck up. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=289810" target="top">Nalianna Kersnovske</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> of <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.codecruncher.com/eh/" target="top">Eternal Heroes</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=izlaaru>Izlaaru</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 183<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/10/03 4:42 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why wizards can't get groups...</span><hr size=1> Euphrates I'll agree with most of what you say, as long as the comments are made AFTER the mistake is made and only as a side comment unless it happens more than once.<br>
<br>
The comments<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
If the wizard is using strike of solusek (or any eye candy nuke) instead of draughts/rains/other more efficient nukes because they like big crits, then I will say something. If the wizard isn't using concussion ENOUGH, I will say something<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
