<br>
I have played high end clerics, enchanters, paladins, wizards, and druids. I think I might know how to play my wizard better than you do. If I pull aggro, its because the tank isn't keeping up. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=erumaroneverbright>Erumaron Everbright</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 271<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/10/03 6:07 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why wizards can't get groups...</span><hr size=1> Euphrates knows cleric, he's 65 in an uber guild of xegony and what not...but yea, using pure draughts limits wizard dps to like 150-170 max in and exp group.  I've parsed SoS / Draught mix and with an SoS crit I can near 300dps on a single mob.  Without crits it's generally ~180-200dps overall (on all mobs for that night).  I even happen to use pure SoS from time to time if the group has a solid tank where I can drop one early in the mobs HP (like...start casting between 90-95%) the parser gives numbers close to 500dps if I were to crit multiple times (and yes..I know it's a bit lower since the nuke didn't hit until like 85% or so).  Where I use purely SoS I was doing roughly half the mobs HP in dmg...draughts is maybe 1/3rd dmg.  Also, the only time I took aggro was when scs3 dinged and I was testing it out.<br>
