                                    Ixthontus   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=santerai>santerai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 133<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/11/03 1:58 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Euphrates ....</span><hr size=1> In exp grps I can start nuking at 80% and manage my nukes so I don't get aggro .... I don't have Concussion, but one of these days I might get bored and do it. I rarely get aggro. If I do happen to get aggro, I stand there and let the tank taunt it off of me. If for some reason the tank sucks at taunting and cant get it off, I root it and back away.<br>
<br>
I have grped with people before who have told me how to play my class. Sorry, but I haven't invested my time in my chosen class for no reason at all, after 61 levels I do like to think that I'm a damn good wizard, and I don't need to be lectured as soon as I join the grp on how to nuke and snare and control aggro. I have also left grps that the people in it would dictate me how to play a wizard. <br>
<br>
I have put in my time on how to play my class. Grping and being a grp friendly wizard is something I'm proud of, I have hardly soloed. Before you start informing me on how to play your version of my class let me show you that I can play my class just fine without any advice from you.<br>
<br>
