<br>
I've had bad experiences with every class, but since this this is mostly about wizards and grouping I will stick with that. Wizards tend to be harder to measure since they really aren't put on the spot as much as clerics, enchanters or warriors, but it's the little things which get noticed and gets remembered.<br>
<br>
The comments from the cleric in Izlaaru's post aren't uncommon, many people do it. But the hard reality is that sometimes bad situations happen so often that it is a surprise when a wizard is actually playing to his potential in a group.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>After that discussion, the SK pulled (good pull) but for some reason the second Guardian agro'd on us. The second wizard in the group (He was 53) ran from the group.. I cast evac and boom we were at the zone in , and everyone cept for the other wizzy (Who decided to run as I said before) was alive and kicking. I was getting tells from the whole group sayin &quot;Wow, what a wizard&quot; and stuff like that. Again WTH? Isn't that our job, shouldn't EVERYONE be doing that type of thing??<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Like here with evac. I've seen far too many wizards who act like that 2nd wizard in that group who would simply run out of the group, and turn yellow at the first sign of trouble. A good wizard can sense when a situation is manageable or isn't, and will evac when it isn't. Sometimes it isn't always obvious at first, which is when an evac call from the enchanter or cleric if he is oom comes into play. Problem is, it seems that good evaccing wizards/druids are a dime a dozen. I must have had the following scenerio happen at least a dozen times: mass adds come in a dungeon, we know we can't make through it and evac is called, wizard/druid says 'ok memming evac', group dies and wizard/druid blames everyone but himself (how dare the group let the mob hit him while he was memming evac?). Others will simply evac just for the heck of it: puller calls 'add one', wizard evacs group without telling anyone or better yet, simply gates or runs. <br>
<br>
So no Izlaaru, the reality is that not everyone is doing that type of thing. After a bad run of wizards in groups, people can be inclined to say 'finally a wizard who actually knows how to evac' once they get a wizard that knows how to play within a group. I know that I take note of such things such as a wizard evaccing when it is needed, rooting and stunning as needed (big ++ on this one, so few wizards actually do it but when they do it is greatly appreciated here), snaring, playing an active role in the group where I know that I can depend on that wizard to be a great member of the group; it's not all about nuking. So be glad, you made a good impression on that group and chances are they will be calling you back for groups later on (if you want them hehe). That 2nd wizard who ran on his group probably won't be called back, and will probably be seen on a later date on Graffe whining about how wizards are always unwanted in groups even though he is supposedly a great wizard.<br>
<br>
